The paper deals with the combinatorial structure of a 3D digital image and its associated cubical complex, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus on cohomology and cup products suggests a connection to algebraic topology and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithmic aspect of computing cup products also suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of polyhedral complexes and their embedding in $\mathbb{R}^3$ suggests a connection to geometric topology (cs.GT) and scientific computing (cs.SI).
